
[1]calamit

   CALAMIT, n. A mineral, probably a variety of Tremolite. It occurs in
   imperfect or rounded prismatic crystals, longitudinally striated, and
   sometimes resembling a reed. Its structure is foliated; its luster
   vitreous, and more or less shining.
